\section*{\LARGE {Abstract}}

The efficient use of new and upcoming technologies is significant when developing software. 
And for which, a real-time tracking system will be used in this project to maximise productivity 
in a courier-based system currently operated by MedLabs to process all the different medical 
samples. Moreover, two applications will be developed, both of which are for MedLabs as well. 
The first application will be used by patients and will provide all the necessary services 
typically present in similar applications. The patients will also be able to fill a form 
requesting a medical sample to be taken from them from their homes. This is currently 
done through the call-center at MedLabs. Which introduces difficulties for the patients as well 
as MedLabs themselves. The second application will be used by the couriers and the admins 
working for MedLabs, with each of them being able to make use of functionalities relevant 
to their roles. A real-time tracking system that uses GPS technology developed by fellow 
students from PSUT's King Abdullah II School of Engineering will be used by the admins 
to assign tasks to the couriers as effectively and efficiently as possible.
